27/11/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- One police officer was killed and another was seriously injured in an attack on their patrol in Skopje on Wednesday (November 26th). A third police officer was slightly hurt in the incident, which happened near the Mathematics Faculty in the northern part of the capital. Interior Minister Gordana Jankulovska suggested the attack may have stemmed from recent successful police operations against organised crime circles. (Vecer, Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 27/11/08; AFP, Makfax - 26/11/08)
